data.title: Lorain Public Library recognizes Toni Morrison poster contest winners
data.meta_description: Born Chloe Anthony Wofford in 1931, Toni Morrison became the first African American woman to win the Nobel Prize for Literature when she was awarded the honor in 1993. Her long list of accomplishments includes earning a Pulitzer Prize in 1988 and a U.S. Presidential Medal of Freedom in 2012.
